                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/1157: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-30T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 30, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Your 136, April 28, 2 p.m. There has been a slight delay in carrying out the
                    defense plans, which however is now being overcome. It is believed that it will
                    be possible to submit the agreement to the legislature toward the latter part of
                    May, when an adequate force will have arrived in Liberia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
